COMMENT: Most people don't realise but aluminium oxidizes. Not like steel but old aluminium (I.e. not new) will have small indents full of oxidized aluminium which new aluminium won't stick to. So before you can weld to aluminium you need to clean that oxidisation off. There's products like alibrite that will actually eat into the aluminium a microscopic amount and remove any impurities. Another method is grinding but you need to go in deep enough to get to the bottom of the holes. Usually a combination of grinding and acetone is enough to prep aluminium for welding but it's still not an easy process. Tig welding is like rubbing your tummy and parting you head but add in stomping your foot swaying your hips

COMMENT: REPENTANCE is required to be hidden from the Lords anger/JUDGMENT DAY!): Seek ye the LORD, all ye meek of the earth, who have upheld his justice; seek righteousness, seek meekness: it may be ye shall be hid in the day of the LORD'S anger. (Zephaniah 2:3). ***(Seek The Lord): This is the language of true (REPENTANCE), renewal, and regeneration. ***(You will be hidden): Zephaniah used a play on words with meaning of his own name, "Hidden in the Lord." Even in the midst of the most calamitous judgment scenes, the mercy and grace of the Lord is still available to a (REPENTANT) people. ***(Luke 13:3)<---Jesus)<---I tell you, Nay: but, except ye (REPENT), ye shall all likewise perish. ***(Luke 5:32)<---(Jesus)<---I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to (REPENTANCE). ***(2 Peter 3:9)<---The Lord is not slack concerning his promise, as some men count slackness; but is longsuffering to us-ward, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to (REPENTANCE). ***(Romans 2:4)<---Or do you disregard the riches of His kindness, tolerance, and patience, not realizing that God's kindness leads you to (REPENTANCE?) * (REPENTANCE): (Greek. Metanoia); Strong's #3341; This Greek word is a compound word derived from meta, meaning "after" and suggesting some type of change, and nous, meaning "mind." Thus the word strictly denotes "a change of mind." But it also connotes remorse for sin, accompanied by a desire to turn away from one's sin, to God, for salvation. Both John the Baptist and Jesus began their ministries with a call to repentance. (See Matthew 3:2, 4:17)---A call that many of the social outcasts and "sinners" of that day answered, (See Luke 19:1-10), but that the religious people rejected. (Luke 11:39-44; 18:9-14).

COMMENT: I think that the whole Magic - Pelinka thing is very similar to the Kobe  - Shaq beef. The Kobe - Shaq beef originally started because to Kobe  basketball was everything. Even if the Lakers won the championship he  would spend his entire summer working on his game, training and staying  in shape. Shaq on the other hand Shaq was like "OK we won the chip, I  won finals MVP (deservingly so ) see you mofos at training camp". Then  he would spend his summer making movies, recording albums, doing his DJ  thing and just living life the way he wanted (not thinking about  basketball at all) which irritated Kobe to no end. So when Shaq would  present himself at training camp fat and out of shape, Kobe would be in  his face.  From this we can assume that Kobe chose someone similar  to him as his agent. Someone who puts 100% effort into what he does no  matter what and isn't distracted by other (in this case non Lakers  things) things. Now we know that Magic likes being Magic and he was  doing a lot of other stuff besides being the GM of the Lakers. Pelinka  was irritated and the whole thing blew up. I'm not defending Pelinka but  I do understand his frustration. It's annoying when you work and your  colleagues don't care as much as you. However it was Magic who signed  Lebron (even though I think he was coming to the Lakers regardless of  Magic) and it will be interesting to see what Pelinka can do on his own  or with another GM. Well this is just my opinion.

COMMENT: To better explain beef terminology as their is a lot of misconceptions.  Like so Sam can see! (:  Wagyu Beef simply means Japanese style Beef. Kobe Beef is wagyu beef but more specifically a breed of black Japanese cattle raised near the city of Kobe. Kobe beef is just a recognizable term for Americans, Matsusaka beef is actually far superior. The American wagyu Beef that Snake river farms sells is a hybrid of the Black Japanese cattle and Angus, which in some ways is the best of both worlds for an Americans palette. Snake river farms is probably the best you can get beef wise in the states without importing proper A5 Wagyu.

COMMENT: Space Time, I have a weird idea about the different quantum theories. On some level, you can almost treat them like the theory is an analogy that takes something we don't understand very well, and treats it like something we do understand, but because it's an analogy, it doesn't always fit. From that view point, the universal theory of everything could be said to be a universal analogy that doesn't break down even when poked and prodded from every angle. If I say "Automobiles are like electrons flowing along a conductor" that analogy works at a certain level, but breaks down in others. Electrons don't break down after a certain mileage, or have carwashes. From that frame of reference (forgive me, I had to) aren't theories like a holographic universe, and string theory, sort of like analogies that take something we can't understand, and get it as close as possible to something we do, but the ideas that are closest to truth are the analogies that hold up to scrutiny and get widely accepted?

COMMENT: Assume for the moment that our universe is a black hole, and its surface is the holographic source of its 3+1D structure and behaviour that we perceive, as posited. Is it possible, then, that any matter or energy that has crossed the event horizon into our universe has left its information at the event horizon and manifests inside our universe as dark matter and dark energy? This inflow of matter and energy provides the engine of the universes expansion, and as it expands its increasing size captures more matter and energy external to it and therefore accelerates the expansion.    From our perspective the edges of the universe disappear as the expansion of space exceeds the speed of light, as the expansion rushes toward but never reaches the edge of the ADS. Would this not also be how the inside of a black hole is perceived, where the escape velocity of any matter exceeds the speed of light, but the space inside the event horizon is expanding toward the edge of the ADS inside the black hole itself as the hole grows? If our universe is growing in size the way a black hole does, then the black holes we see inside our own 'black hole' would reflect the scale invariance of the universe.    Even though black holes inside our universe start out as ordinary matter and energy thats swallowed by an event horizon emanating outward from the black holes centre of mass (eg, originally from a large supernova remnant), is it then possible that the imprinting of this originating matter on the event horizon doesnt actually destroy its localised information characteristics that we measure (as fermions, bosons, etc in 3+1D), as distinct from matter being sucked in from outside which leaves everything at the door? Its difficult to justify such an artificial distinction, but if it exists then this may be a way to understand the origins of dark energy and matter.    Just some thoughts, which surely violate numerous fundamental principles and physical laws.
VIDEONAME: The Holographic Universe Explained

COMMENT: Dirk IS the Mavericks ! I remember playing an NBA game on my Gameboy when I was a kid and already back then Dirk was the face of the franchise and he will always be associated with them and them with him. He is one of the basketball great, one of those who changed the game ! This was such a great retirement ceremony, great to see other retired players who were his role models having his back and joining him on this evening. I was hoping Dirk would tell some more stories he remembers, some highlights of his career, but standing in the center of the arena and everything being about YOU, being out of words is the only reasonable thing. It always hurts seeing these talented people becoming too old and seeing how short life is, but he sure did the best out of it. Basketball enabled him, he enabled basketball. A great sport a lot of people love and he perfected it in his way. An inspiration off and on the court, a legend. #41-21-1
